<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="jn1015b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="jn1" href="#jn1015">JN1: </a>  <a href="../../FF/unbs/jn1all.htm#jn1015b"> (NLI.2A) 15(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <p class="set">Modest, and fair, for fair and good are near <br> &nbsp; Neighbours, howe&apos;re.? <br>No noble virtue ever was alone, <br> &nbsp; But two in one. <br>Then, when I praise sweet modesty, I praise <br> &nbsp; Bright beauty&apos;s rays: <br>And having praised both beauty and modesty, <br> &nbsp; I have praised thee.</p> <p class="diip"> <u>Ben Johnson</u></p> <p class="spbr">======= in his play &mdash; &ldquo;Epicene or The Silent Woman&rdquo; =======</p> </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: <cite>The Works of Ben Jonson</cite>, ed. William Gifford (London: Nicol, 1816), <a href="https://archive.org/details/worksofbenjonson03jonsuoft/page/374/mode/2up" target="_blank">Vol. III: &ldquo;The Silent Woman&rdquo;, p. 374</a></mm> </dd></dl>
